item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: richard
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Leicester City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Leicester community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Almost ready for the off!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Summer is here...and so is the FreeSpirit Summer Camp. This year we return to the lovely location of Lochgoilhead. Come back often as we will be updating these pages every day. Please do join in and leave us your comments.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Good luck and best wishes guys! You'll almost do 500 miles, so you'll be doing 500 more!

Here's a useful link for you to get into the lingo, a Scottish Vernacular Dictionary :)
http://www.firstfoot.com/dictionary

item.title: And we're off!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The most glorious morning arrived...the start of Summer Camp, and this year we were back to our favourite activity centre for a week of fun in the highlands of Scotland. An early start (6am at the hut) saw FreeSpirit ESU and BrakeStone Network loading their kit onto the mini-bus for the long drive to the Lochgoilhead Scout Activity Centre. Our first break was just past Birmingham on the M6 - Hilton Services, and a much needed pint of coffee. Upon arriving back at our trusty minibus, Sam discovered Myfanwy...the first of our new mascots! Our Second stop was at Lancaster after an hours detour due to the M6 being closed courtesy of a "flour" incident...and again a mysterious new mascot had arrived...Mr Duck! Our final stop and late lunch was at Gretna Green Services just over the boarder...before a final sprint and an arrival at the centre around 4.30pm

item.title: Dinner, Programme and Card Against Humanity...
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Our kit was unloaded, our beds were chosen and dinner arrived. This was preceded by a leaders meeting where our weeks programme was confirmed. Before the Leaders and Network headed off into the lounge for a round or two of "Cards of Humanity"...the start of a great week! ...the view from our bedroom window.

item.title: The Ladder Challenge!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Following a cooked breakfast and flagbreak, we headed over to the equipment room to kit up in a full harness...our challenge for the next hour and a half, was to get as many of our Unit to the top of the ladder. This was a test of teamwork...and ones ability to come to terms with scary heights! Stunning achievements by all, but especially tom and Harry.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: My god. History has been made. Tom getting above ground level!

item.title: Sunset around the Loch
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Early evening saw one or two of us exploring around the loch. The village is quite small but very picturesque...

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Lovely views, hope the midges weren't too hungry!

item.title: Mad man with a bow!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Immediately following Jacob's challenge...we headed into the archery range, and found that Rob is a mean dude with a bow - don't mess with this guy!

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Shot through the heart and you're to blame, you give archery a bad name! :) Well done everyone!

item.title: Explorers vs Network...the raft challenge
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The afternoon's activity was to design and build a raft...then race it across the loch! It was decided that FreeSpirit wanted to compete against Brakestone...a decision that they were to regret later on. FreeSpirit's design looked compact and safe, whilst Brakestone's design looked more radical...but would it be stable? BrakeStone's design proved more stable and were a clear winner!

item.title: Poker, Yu Gi-oh and film night
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Following an excellent roast chicken dinner, we commandeered a meeting room within the centre. At this point both Units went into chill mode...the poker school resumed, a Yu Gi-oh game started, onsie's were worn, cards were underway...and we suffered a shark attack!   ...and the late night film beckons! I believe that tonight's showing is Abraham Lincoln, Vampire Slayer...a classic! (not!!)

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Didn't know there were sharks in the loch! Did it get you whilst rafting?
Du dum du dum du dum dudumdumdumdudumdudumm arrgh
Quick the shark has eaten the dowsells. He'll soon spit them out

item.title: Flagbreak...with Mad Alice!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Monday was our turn to do flagbreak...so we decided to combine it with an investiture - our newest leader, Mad Alice. We have enticed her over to Explorer Scouting from the dark side (Cubs Scouts!). Welcome to FreeSpirit.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Well done Alice! If you can handle cubs, anything after is child's play :)

item.title: A few funny moments!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: There have been many funny moments (and we're only on day 3)...so please enjoy round 1!

item.title: Water, water, a sinking and a canoe!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Our morning activity today was Canoeing. We paired up, grabbed a canoe and headed out across the lake...Jon and Tom now hold the record for the most swims...and Maddy and Holly for the most decorative way to wear seaweed! Our instructor (Ella) almost incurred our wrath...when she duck-napped Mr Duck and dragged him behind her canoe...she seen saw the error of her ways.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: I see you found a sea horse at the loch too. Definitely something fishy going on there!

item.title: What a view!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Our afternoon activity today was climbing and abseiling...and the forecast was scattered showers! It was going to be interesting. There was a short walk from the centre up to a crag overlooking the site and the loch...and the view from the top was amazing. Most of the group had a decent of the cliff face...and in many cases, personal fears were triumphed. Well done to everyone who had a go - especially Harry and Maddy.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: My son needs to look less grumpy in photos, especially when he's about to jump off a cliff! :D

item.title: Eurgh. Windburn
item.dc:creator: Alice

item.title: ALICE
item.dc:creator: Explorers

item.title: Sunset around the loch...part 2
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Tonight's stroll around the loch with the camera produced a couple of photo opportunities...before retiring to the common room for a few games of "One Night Ultimate Werewolf"!

item.title: Wind, water...and a sailing dinghy
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: After our usual hearty breakfast, we suited up and headed out onto the loch for a morning sailing. A few silly games later found most of us still dry...and then the racing began! ...a good morning.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Excellent day, think we've had most of the rain you should have had in Scotland down here in Wellington! Glad to see smiles all round today :)

item.title: The Burn Run!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: What an afternoon! Probably our best activity yet. We headed up the mountain from the centre until we arrived on the banks of a local mountain stream...and after the rain, it was flowing nicely! We then proceeded to climb into the river and make our way upstream clambering over boulders, plunging into pools, walking behind waterfalls and exploring overhangs. The chasm of doom!! Deep under the overhang... Balancing above the waterfall...

item.title: Burn run... or slightly charred jog....
item.dc:creator: Alice
item.content:encoded:
I am so so proud of my little camp family! They were all super fab today, working together to get me up the gorge. They encouraged me, helped me, supported me, dragged me, pushed me and didn't laugh when I fell over!
They worked fluidly as a unit and I am super stoked to be part of Freespirit. Day off tomorrow... thank God. Today nearly broke me Camp Mam x

item.title: A rest day in Oban
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Today we had a day off centre activities...so we all piled into the "fun bus" and headed over to Oban where a day of wandering through this lovely seaside town beckoned. The leaders headed to the top of the town and the Colosseum-like structure that is McCaig Tower, before indulging in a local delicacy - haggis and chips!

item.title: The World Water-slide Championships!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: FreeSpirit has been coming to Lochgoilhead since 2008. It has always been a tradition to hold a water-slide championships, and this year was no exception. The competition was fierce...a combination of technique, speed (and body weight) was needed to stand on top of the podium!

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Alice if you'd left the water wings off you'd have won it easily

item.title: An extremely tiring Cobbler!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Today was our opportunity to take a "small" walk in the hills! Our intrepid instructors, Luke and Liam, directed us to a loch side car park at the far side of Loch Long. From here, our walk led us onwards and upwards into the mountains for the day. Accompanying us were Graham Simpson (MSP for Central Scotland) and his main right hand man and communications Officer, Danny. 900 meters, and a few hours later, found us at the summit of The Cobbler. We then descended off the back of the mountain and headed down the other ridge until the drop off. A fairly steep decent through very wet grass until we finally stumbled back into the car park...totally shattered, and home for tea.

item.title: A very nervous mother duck...
item.dc:creator: Alice
item.content:encoded: So today, I sent my camp family off into the wilderness whilst Mam stayed home and baked treats. It was hard fitting my home made wares into a jaffa cake box but I managed it! I waited nervously... in the pub... drinking lattes and reading the paper!

item.title: Sailing and an Abseil
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Our last day dawned wet and windy and we had a six hour sail to do! Our outward leg, had us tacking down the loch for two and half hours. Everyone had an opportunity to take the helm and trim the sails. Our destination was a lovely crag...and, following lunch, a great abseil was had by all.

item.title: ...the final word!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: After a 9.5 hour drive south, we pulled into the car park at our Scout Hut...the sun was shining and all the parents were there to welcome us. ...our Scottish adventure had come to a close - til the next time! A fantastic week; new friends; new activities; an excellent venue - a brilliant bunch of Explorer Scouts and Network Scouts. Many thanks to my fellow leaders, without which this highlight of the year could not happen.
